The size of Italy's national debt increased to record figures
Italy's national debt in June 2016 exceeded 2,248 trillion euros.
The country's central bank said that this amount is a historic high, RIA Novosti reported.
The previous negative record was set in May of this year.
Then the size of the national debt reached 2.228 trillion euros.
It is noted that in the first half of the year, Italy's debt load increased by 77.2 billion euros.
Earlier it was reported that at the end of 2015, Italy's national debt was 132.7% of the country's GDP.
Meanwhile, Italian Minister of Economy and Finance Pier Carlo Padoan predicted a decline in this figure in 2016 to 130.9%, and in 2018 to 123.4% of GDP.
Payments from the airport received 141 victims of the terrorist attack in "Domodedovo."
141 people received charitable payments from the "Aviation Fund," which was created by the management of the airport "Domodedovo" to help the victims of the terrorist attack in 2011, reports Interfax.
According to the press secretary of the airport Alexander Vlasov, two more statements are under consideration.
"On the part of the Fund, charitable payments to victims of the 2011 terrorist attack are continuing and comprehensive assistance is being provided to resolve existing issues," Vlasov added, recalling that a fund website containing full information on the procedure for the provision of charitable assistance was created specifically to facilitate interaction with the victims.
In 2011, in the arrival hall of foreign airlines Domodedovo, a suicide bomber detonated an explosive device.
As a result of the terrorist attack, 37 people were killed, another 172 were injured.
Scientists have found an animal that can live 500 years
An international biologist has concluded that the longest-lived vertebrate animal is the Greenland polar shark, which can live about 500 years.
Scientists conducted a radiocarbon analysis of the lens of the eye of 28 Greenland sharks.
The largest shark, which is longer than five meters long, can be from 272 to 512 years.
Biologists believe that an important role in the longevity of the shark is played by low metabolism, which leads to slow development.
Greenland sharks reach puberty only by the age of 150.
Previously, it was believed that the longest of all vertebrate animals live "neighbor" sharks - the Greenland whale.
The oldest specimen known to scientists was a little older than 210 years.
