What does it mean that Russia is emerging from the crisis?
Economists have seen signs of Russia's withdrawal from the longest recession in the last 20 years.
According to Bloomberg analysts, Russia's GDP shows a positive dynamics - in the second quarter of GDP decreased by 0.8% in annual terms.
This is the lowest since the beginning of 2015.
According to the latest data of Rosstat, the decline of the Russian economy in the second quarter slowed to 0.6%.
The Central Bank and the Ministry of Economic Development also announced the stabilization of the situation.
Ahead is slow growth.
According to experts of the Central Bank, the recession in the Russian economy is a thing of the past.
"The indicative estimate of Russian GDP suggests that the recession is behind, and ahead - slow growth of the economy," - stated in the bulletin of the Bank of Russia "What are the trends say."
The modular estimate of GDP for the current quarter, the regulator's specialists increased to 0.4%, the estimate for the fourth quarter is 0.5%.
According to the representative of the Ministry of Economic Development, during the second quarter, the decline in the GDP of the Russian Federation stopped in the second quarter, amounting to 0.2%.
In the second quarter, the seasonally cleared GDP decline was 0.2% compared to the previous quarter.
But during the quarter, the decline stopped: in April it was 0.2%, and in May and June, the change in GDP was in the range of 0-0.15," - quotes the representative of the Ministry of Economics of RIA Novosti.
The slowdown in the pace of the fall of the Russian economy over the past five quarters indicates that "the bottom has been passed."
Among other markers pointing to signs of a revival of the national economy, Bloomberg calls the growth of demand for electricity and rail transportation, the revival of business.
If you make an amendment that the year is leap year, it is clear that the dynamics of plus 1% of electricity consumption can be half due to an additional working day.
Add to this a lower average annual temperature in the first quarter.
The next argument is the growth of freight traffic, but it is difficult to obtain accurate data, and plus or minus 0.5% of the semi-annual volume can also be explained by seasonality," explains Kirill Yakovenko of ALOR BROKER.
However, there are other, more obvious signs of stabilizing the Russian economy.
For example, lower price pressure.
In July, the consumer price index was 7.2% compared to 15.6% in the same month last year.
Moreover, for the last two weeks, Rosstat has recorded deflation.
Prices in Russia fell for the first time in five years.
If you look at the dynamics of the ruble, which, although it showed strong fluctuations at the beginning of the year, by the end of August from the beginning of the year strengthened by 12%.
This is also one of the signs of recovery, which should be followed by indicators from the real sector of the economy," Yakovenko emphasizes.
In addition, since April, the Russian Federation has seen an increase in industrial production.
In June, the figure grew by 1.7%.
The rate of decline in foreign trade turnover is slowing from -32.8% in January 2016 to -20.7% in May.
The situation in the labor market, where the unemployment rate has fallen to 5.4%, also demonstrates positive dynamics.
It was only in September 2015 (5.2 percent).
Despite the well-off situation in the labor market, the issue with the real disposable incomes of the population to leave much to be desired.
In annual terms, the indicator decreases by 4.8%.
This factor can hamper the economic recovery, as household spending contributes a considerable contribution to GDP.
As a rule, in the structure of the economy, their share exceeds 50%.
In addition to low consumer activity, the Bank of Russia's strict policy can also be called as risk factors for economic growth.
The regulator holds the rate at 10.5%, which does not have the best effect on the real sector.
The negative factor is the insufficient level of investment, which hinders the development of industrial potential.
But in general, it can be assumed that by the end of the year the pace of the decline of the Russian economy will slow to -0.5% against -3.7% in 2015," says Irina Rogova, analyst at Forex Club.
