But to say that she was raised by our coaches in Russia, it would be wrong.
Soon, the girl's family decided to emigrate to the United States and settle in the city of Colorado.
Mary continued her classes.
She was soon a member of the U.S. national team and showed great results at the Pan American Games.
It is clear that at a serious international level, Russian synchronists can not compete, but for America its indicators - the ceiling.
The new name, which in Russian sounds strange, Christina Shaldybina received at the age of 11, when her parents decided to continue the girl's rhythmic gymnastics overseas.
