The last in our list is the Chechen boxer, born in 1995 in the capital of Dagestan Makhachkala - Arthur Biyarslanov.
When the boy was ten years old, his parents took their family through Azerbaijan to Canada.
There, Arthur, on the advice of his older brother, began boxing.
Since then, Arthur has become the champion of Canada three times, and in 2012 he became the world champion among young people.
