On Friday, August 12, 2016, the Central Bank of Russia revoked the license for banking operations from the credit institution Joint Stock Commercial Bank "GAZSTRUYBANK," registered in Moscow.
According to the regulator, JSC GAZSTROYYBK carried out a high-risk credit policy related to the placement of funds in low-quality assets.
Adequate assessment of the risks taken at the request of the supervisory authority and a reliable reflection of the value of the bank's assets led to the emergence of the credit institution grounds for the implementation of measures to prevent bankruptcy.
In addition, the credit institution was involved in dubious transit operations.
The bank appointed a temporary administration for a period of validity until the appointment to the competitive manager or liquidator.
The powers of the executive bodies of the credit institution in accordance with federal laws have been suspended.
JSCB "GAZSTROYBANK" is a participant of the deposit insurance system.
Recall that the payment of insurance compensation to depositors of the bank, including individual entrepreneurs, in accordance with Federal Law No. 177-FZ "On insurance of deposits of individuals in banks of the Russian Federation" is provided in the amount of 100% of the balance of funds, but not more than 1.4 million rubles. in total for one depositor.
Payments, according to the Deposit Insurance Agency, will begin no later than August 26, 2016.
According to the reporting data, the assets of JSC JSC "GASSTROYBANK" as of August 1, 2016 It took 335th place in the banking system of the Russian Federation.
