The government has extended the period of destruction of sanctions products
The government has extended until the end of 2017 the destruction of food products banned from importing to Russia.
The corresponding resolution was signed by Prime Minister Dmitry Medvedev, it was published on the official portal of legal information.
The embargo against countries that imposed anti-Russian sanctions due to the situation in Ukraine was introduced in our country in August 2014.
Subsequently, the ban has been repeatedly extended, now it is valid until December 31, 2017.
It is forbidden to import some types of agricultural products, raw materials and food from the United States, the European Union, Canada, Australia, Norway, Ukraine, Albania, Montenegro, Iceland and Liechtenstein.
In particular, the ban included meat and meat products, fish, seafood, vegetables, fruits and dairy products.
Disposal of food imported into the country bypassing the embargo has been carried out in Russia since August 2015.
In the first quarter of 2016 alone, about 100 tons of prohibited products were withdrawn from the sale.
