FAS fined Google almost half a billion rubles
The reason was a violation of competition in the mobile application market.
The antimonopoly proceedings were initiated by Yandex.
The Russian company claimed that Google provides smartphone manufacturers with access to Android components on terms that banned the pre-installation of applications from other developers, in particular, from Yandex.
